<title>UK: Avalon Oil Plc sets first day premium.</title>
<headline>Avalon Oil Plc sets first day premium.</headline>
<dateline>LONDON 1997-04-01</dateline>
<text>
<p>Shares in Avalon Oil Plc, a U.S.-based oil exploration and production company, set a premium on their first day on London Stock Exchange's Alternative Investment Market (AIM) on Tuesday.</p>
<p>By 1445 GMT, the shares were quoted at 103-1/2p, above their issue price of 100p, although no trade was recorded in the stock.</p>
<p>Avalon Oil said it raised around 31.7 million stg with the issue, which will go to finance a Russian joint venture with Orenburggazprom, a subsidiary of Russian gas monopoly RAO Gazprom.</p>
<p>Avalon, which is based in Oklahoma, said it was valued at 76.0 million stg at the issue price.</p>
<p>The broker to the issue was Henderson Crosthwaite.</p>
<p>-- John Sutherland, London Newsroom +44 171 542 7945</p>
